name: fortinet-forticlient-ems
label: Fortinet FortiClient EMS
description: FortiClient Enterprise Management Server (FortiClient EMS) is a security management solution that enables scalable and centralized management of multiple endpoints (computers).This connector provides operations related to quarantine/unquarantine endpoints, get endpoint details, etc

fields.title: Server URL
fields.description: The URL of the FortiClient EMS server to which you will connect and perform automated operations.
fields.name: server

fields.title: Username
fields.tooltip: Username of EMS server or Type domain name\domain user name or domain netbios name\domain user name to log in via a domain
fields.description: The username used to access the FortiClient EMS server to which you will connect and perform the automated operations.
fields.name: username

fields.title: Password
fields.description: The Password used to access the FortiClient EMS server to which you will connect and perform the automated operations.
fields.name: password

fields.title: Verify SSL
fields.name: verify_ssl
fields.description: Specifies whether the SSL certificate for the server is to be verified or not.

operations.title: Get All Endpoints
operations.description: Retrieves a list of all the endpoints or the specific endpoints connected to the specified Fortinet FortiClient EMS server based on the input parameters you have specified.

parameters.title: Activity
parameters.tooltip: Select the activity based on which you want to filter the endpoints retrieved from FortiClient EMS. You can choose from the following options: EMS On Net, EMS Off Net, or Total.
parameters.name: activity
parameters.description: Select the activity based on which you want to filter the endpoints retrieved from FortiClient EMS. You can choose from the following options: EMS On Net, EMS Off Net, or Total.

parameters.description: Select the connection based on which you want to filter the endpoints retrieved from FortiClient EMS. You can choose from the following options: Online, OfflineLong, OfflineNominal, OfflineRecent, or Total.

parameters.title: Sort Order
parameters.tooltip: Select the checkbox (by default it is selected) to sort the endpoints retrieved from FortiClient EMS in an 'ascending' order.
parameters.name: order_asc

parameters.title: Count
parameters.tooltip: Specify the maximum number of results, per page, that this operation should return in its response.
parameters.name: count
parameters.description: Specify the maximum number of results, per page, that this operation should return in its response.

parameters.title: Offset
parameters.tooltip: Specify the index of the first item to be returned by this operation. This parameter is useful if you want to get a subset of records, say endpoints starting from the 10th endpoint. By default, this is set as 0.
parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: Specify the index of the first item to be returned by this operation. This parameter is useful if you want to get a subset of records, say endpoints starting from the 10th endpoint. By default, this is set as 0.

operations.title: Quarantine Endpoints
operations.description: Quarantines the specified endpoints on the Fortinet FortiClient EMS server based on the endpoint IDs you have specified.

parameters.tooltip: Specify the IDs of the endpoints to quarantine on the Fortinet FortiClient EMS server.
parameters.name: ids
